Students said they were protesting against curriculum changes and a lack of funding from the National Student Financial Aid Scheme. JOHANNESBURG - Protesting students at Wits University have dispersed and all entrances are now open at the education campus in Parktown. Earlier, around 150 students were refusing to allow people in or out of the premises. Students say they were protesting against curriculum changes and a lack of funding from the National Student Financial Aid Scheme. They say they ll resume their demonstration on Friday and expect vice chancellor Adam Habib to address them.Wits University s Sharona Patel says, All the gates at the Wits Education Campus have been opened and cleared, and staff and students who are still on campus can leave freely. The majority of them had left earlier already. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)